#X text 26 20 The rightmost inlet takes impulses to sync all oscillators. The 'sync' message into the left inlet is the control rate trigger version. By default (mode 0) \, we have random phases for each. In mode 1 we have an initial random value and we sync to it every time. Mode 2 syncs to a deterministic list of phases based on the golden ratio. Mode 4 resets all phases to 0 \, which makes it sound quite flangy. You can also use the 'syncmode' flag to set the mode at initialization.;
#X obj 83 324 else/superosc~ 150 0 25, f 14;
