#X obj 90 355 else/superosc~ 110 0 50;
#X text 20 11 By default we have a spread value of '1' \, which is a maximum spread over the stereo field. You can also set to '0' \, where all oscillators are at the center for both outputs (hence \, an equal or duplicated mono output). Of couse you can also set from anywhere in between (from 0 to 1). If you only have one oscillator \, this parameter and the spread curve has no effect. For two or three oscillators \, the spread curve has no effect either. For two oscillators \, they are hard panned to left/right \, ehereas for three oscillators there's a center positioned one. The curve affects the position of oscillators that fall in between 0 and the extremes., f 62;
#X text 20 138 The default curve is "1" \, which evenly spreads the oscillators on the stereo field. The curve values are from 0.1 to 10 and closer to 0.1 makes the in between oscillators more closely to outer extremes \, whereas values near 10 make them closer to the center., f 62;
