#X text 33 15 You can have any number of oscillators (from 1 to 16). A mix parameter sets the gain for the oscillators according to the mixmode. For an odd number of oscillators we have a center one that always has a fixed amplitude value of 1 \, whereas an even number of oscillators have the two center ones also with the same fixed value (1). Hence \, for a number of oscillators that is equal to 1 or 2 \, the mix parameter or mixmode has no effect!, f 70;
#X text 33 99 The mix parameter sets the mix of the outer oscillators. At a mix value of 1 \, all oscillators reach the maximum amplitude (which is 1). The default value is 0.5 and the default mode (mode 0) has more weight to the oscillators that are closer to the center frequency. Mode 1 has more weight on the outer ones. Mode 2 has equal weight on all the outer oscillators. Anyway \, at a mix value of 1 \, all oscillators are equal to 1 in any given mode. Likewise \, a mix of 0 only has the center oscillators in all modes., f 70;
#X text 223 288 equal weigth on outter oscillators;
#X obj 112 368 else/superosc~ -n 3 110 0 50;
